cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this framework, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Principles of Earned Autonomy: A Governance Framework for Autonomous Agents"
abstract: >
  Theory-level framework establishing how autonomous AI agents earn and exercise
  authority. Defines two core problems (autonomous reasoning and earned autonomy),
  three architectural principles (Commander's Intent, Observable Autonomy,
  Convergence Is Silence), and one measurable property (Autonomous Reasoning
  Fidelity, ARF). ARF is operationally defined with technique ancestry (Winograd
  Schema Challenge, CheckList), a defined contrastive-pair probe structure, a
  falsifiable claim, and a formalization agenda. Includes conformance tests for
  all three principles and for ARF, empirical evidence from a three-family
  silence-convergence test (Anthropic, xAI/Grok, Google/Gemini), documented
  falsification findings that bound the convergence claim, and a formal References
  section with seven bibliographic entries. Implementation-agnostic.
